# üì∞ Fake News Classifier

A machine learning project to classify news articles as **real** or **fake**.  
This project uses Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques and supervised learning models.

---

## ‚ú® Features
- Preprocessing of text data (tokenization, stopword removal, vectorization).
- Multiple machine learning models for classification.
- Evaluation using accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.
- Jupyter Notebook included for step-by-step explanation.

---

## üß† Models Used
- **Logistic Regression** ‚Üí A simple yet effective linear model that works well for binary classification tasks like detecting fake vs. real news.  
- **Naive Bayes** ‚Üí A probabilistic model based on Bayes‚Äô theorem. It is very efficient for text classification problems because it assumes feature independence.  
- **Random Forest** ‚Üí An ensemble method that builds multiple decision trees and combines their predictions for better accuracy and robustness.  
- **XGBoost** ‚Üí A powerful gradient boosting algorithm that is optimized for speed and performance. It often achieves high accuracy in classification tasks.

---

## üìä Dataset
This project uses the **Fake News Classification dataset** available on Kaggle:  
[Fake News Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/saurabhshahane/fake-news-classification/data)

‚ö†Ô∏è **Note:** The dataset is not included in this repository due to size limitations.  
Please download it from Kaggle and place it inside a folder named `data/` in the project root.

